1
00:00:48,339 --> 00:00:52,969
DEAR X

2
00:00:53,845 --> 00:00:55,889
ALL CHARACTERS, PLACES, AND EVENTS
IN THIS WORK ARE FICTITIOUS

3
00:00:55,972 --> 00:00:57,515
CHILD ACTORS WERE FILMED
WITH GUARDIANS PRESENT

4
00:02:08,878 --> 00:02:10,130
Two, three. Clear!

5
00:02:19,055 --> 00:02:21,724
CARDIAC PACEMAKER

6
00:02:48,751 --> 00:02:50,253
- One, two, three. Clear!
- At that fork

7
00:02:51,129 --> 00:02:53,631
where one life stands
between life and death

8
00:02:55,758 --> 00:02:57,886
what kind of prayer
did desperate Ah-jin

9
00:02:59,554 --> 00:03:01,055
offer up?

10
00:03:03,558 --> 00:03:05,018
At death's door

11
00:03:06,394 --> 00:03:08,021
was that one's life

12
00:03:09,606 --> 00:03:10,607
or one's end?

13
00:03:23,286 --> 00:03:24,287
Was that death

14
00:03:26,080 --> 00:03:28,499
God's answer to Ah-jin's prayer

15
00:03:30,293 --> 00:03:31,294
or His punishment?

16
00:03:46,434 --> 00:03:47,435
WITH DEEPEST CONDOLENCES

17
00:04:46,160 --> 00:04:47,161
No!

18
00:04:55,920 --> 00:04:57,588
Grandma!

19
00:05:24,699 --> 00:05:29,620
EPISODE 8: BEFORE JUDGMENT

20
00:05:32,415 --> 00:05:34,959
SAMYUN SEOUL HOSPITAL MEMORIAL HALL

21
00:05:35,043 --> 00:05:37,462
NOTICE REGARDING MEDIA COVERAGE

22
00:06:31,182 --> 00:06:33,559
REST IN PEACE

23
00:06:37,772 --> 00:06:38,898
Get some rest.

24
00:06:38,981 --> 00:06:40,483
You'll collapse at this rate.

25
00:06:40,566 --> 00:06:42,318
I'll take him outside for a moment.

26
00:06:45,571 --> 00:06:47,365
HONG KYUNG-SUK

27
00:06:54,831 --> 00:06:56,874
- You two know each other?
- Yes.

28
00:06:56,958 --> 00:06:58,709
He helped me out a lot.

29
00:06:58,793 --> 00:07:01,587
And I worked part-time
at his café for a year.

30
00:07:05,675 --> 00:07:09,804
BASEBALL PLAYER CHOI ARRESTED
FOR MURDERING A PART-TIMER'S FATHER

31
00:07:09,887 --> 00:07:12,140
PARTIALLY ADMITTED GUILT
AND SAID "IT WAS IMPULSIVE"

32
00:07:24,694 --> 00:07:26,821
I was going to go home

33
00:07:28,156 --> 00:07:29,490
after In-gang left.

34
00:07:31,242 --> 00:07:32,910
But I went to her place instead.

35
00:07:35,288 --> 00:07:37,081
He had asked me

36
00:07:38,833 --> 00:07:43,796
and I remembered she hasn't been
sleeping well at night lately.

37
00:07:46,340 --> 00:07:48,551
I wanted to keep her company.

38
00:07:48,634 --> 00:07:51,804
I thought of you
as a gift from my daughter.

39
00:07:53,723 --> 00:07:57,310
I scolded In-gang for doubting you
and pushing you away.

40
00:07:58,811 --> 00:08:00,521
I reprimanded him for that.

41
00:08:01,439 --> 00:08:04,775
You looked so pitiful
when I first saw you

42
00:08:04,859 --> 00:08:07,111
so I believed
you could never do such a thing.

43
00:08:07,862 --> 00:08:08,863
The one who deceived me...

44
00:08:09,489 --> 00:08:10,490
No.

45
00:08:10,990 --> 00:08:12,950
The one who deceived my whole family!

46
00:08:14,118 --> 00:08:15,912
I foolishly trusted you

47
00:08:16,662 --> 00:08:19,624
and I drove my own grandson...

48
00:08:21,667 --> 00:08:23,628
into a bottomless pit.

49
00:08:29,967 --> 00:08:30,968
What...

50
00:08:31,886 --> 00:08:33,346
What should I do?

51
00:08:35,181 --> 00:08:37,558
What am I supposed to do now, Ah-jin?

52
00:08:39,852 --> 00:08:42,980
Can you explain what happened

53
00:08:43,064 --> 00:08:45,566
before and after the fall?

54
00:08:50,446 --> 00:08:51,656
A cat.

55
00:08:54,033 --> 00:08:55,993
She went out to show me

56
00:08:57,495 --> 00:09:00,498
the kitten that had come by.

57
00:09:01,999 --> 00:09:03,000
A cat?

58
00:09:05,378 --> 00:09:06,587
She used to feed

59
00:09:07,922 --> 00:09:10,925
the stray cats in the neighborhood.

60
00:09:11,175 --> 00:09:15,263
In-mo is allergic,
so she couldn't let them inside.

61
00:09:18,015 --> 00:09:21,060
She had only put food out for them.

62
00:09:22,353 --> 00:09:26,357
Sometimes, the cats would bring
their kittens

63
00:09:26,983 --> 00:09:28,234
and show up at her door

64
00:09:29,485 --> 00:09:31,362
at night.

65
00:09:32,071 --> 00:09:33,072
Please continue.

66
00:09:34,532 --> 00:09:36,617
After putting food out for them...

67
00:09:38,953 --> 00:09:40,288
she was standing up...

68
00:09:42,498 --> 00:09:46,335
when she suddenly swayed
as if she got dizzy.

69
00:09:56,929 --> 00:09:58,472
Then, she lost consciousness.

70
00:10:05,438 --> 00:10:06,439
I see.

71
00:10:07,356 --> 00:10:09,150
I know this is hard

72
00:10:10,568 --> 00:10:12,236
but I have a few more questions.

73
00:10:31,714 --> 00:10:32,798
I'll take care of it.

74
00:10:33,633 --> 00:10:35,843
I'll wipe every security camera
and dash cam clean

75
00:10:37,470 --> 00:10:38,679
so get her away from here.

76
00:10:39,180 --> 00:10:41,182
It's more natural
to say that I was here.

77
00:10:43,184 --> 00:10:44,894
And there aren't
any security cameras here.

78
00:10:46,562 --> 00:10:47,813
Don't do anything stupid.

79
00:11:02,578 --> 00:11:05,331
A grandma fell down the stairs.

80
00:11:07,625 --> 00:11:08,751
Please hurry.

81
00:11:19,804 --> 00:11:20,805
Wait!

82
00:11:24,058 --> 00:11:26,519
I'd like to know
exactly what kind of relationship

83
00:11:26,936 --> 00:11:28,229
you have with Baek Ah-jin.

84
00:11:28,604 --> 00:11:29,772
I looked you up.

85
00:11:30,147 --> 00:11:32,024
The Nojeong-dong Rooftop Murder Case.

86
00:11:32,650 --> 00:11:35,528
What does that have to do
with Dharma Sister Yeonhwa's passing?

87
00:11:35,611 --> 00:11:37,363
I read that you testified
you were caught in a trap

88
00:11:37,446 --> 00:11:39,949
set by the victim's daughter,
who worked part-time at your café.

89
00:11:40,032 --> 00:11:42,034
What exactly are you trying to ask?

90
00:11:42,952 --> 00:11:45,621
Is it whether there's a link

91
00:11:45,705 --> 00:11:47,790
between Baek Ah-jin
and her father's murder?

92
00:11:47,873 --> 00:11:49,166
Can you answer that?

93
00:11:49,917 --> 00:11:51,210
You want an answer?

94
00:11:55,881 --> 00:11:57,967
Between the murder
of Mr. Baek Seon-gyu...

95
00:12:00,094 --> 00:12:01,804
and Ms. Baek Ah-jin...

96
00:12:05,975 --> 00:12:06,976
there is no connection.

97
00:12:07,852 --> 00:12:08,853
Sorry?

98
00:12:08,936 --> 00:12:10,479
No connection whatsoever.

99
00:12:11,313 --> 00:12:14,024
Back then, I testified like that
out of a cowardly wish

100
00:12:14,108 --> 00:12:16,861
to slip through the law
because I was afraid

101
00:12:16,944 --> 00:12:18,362
of becoming a criminal.

102
00:12:19,405 --> 00:12:20,906
Which I regret now.

103
00:12:22,199 --> 00:12:26,078
I served five years
and paid for my crime behind bars

104
00:12:26,871 --> 00:12:28,372
but my debt to the deceased

105
00:12:29,623 --> 00:12:31,584
is something I must carry for life.

106
00:12:34,211 --> 00:12:35,296
Baek Ah-jin is

107
00:12:36,130 --> 00:12:38,966
simply a bereaved daughter
who lost her family.

108
00:12:39,049 --> 00:12:40,259
She's someone

109
00:12:41,093 --> 00:12:42,887
I must keep apologizing to
until the day I die.

110
00:12:43,512 --> 00:12:45,723
Since she became so famous

111
00:12:46,515 --> 00:12:49,935
there will inevitably be
all kinds of rumors.

112
00:12:50,019 --> 00:12:51,937
But they're baseless.

113
00:12:52,605 --> 00:12:53,606
I'm relieved to hear that.

114
00:12:54,398 --> 00:12:55,858
Thank you for coming.

115
00:13:05,618 --> 00:13:07,369
Why did you tell him that?

116
00:13:14,835 --> 00:13:16,212
It was a chance to get revenge.

117
00:13:19,757 --> 00:13:21,050
Why defend me?

118
00:13:27,807 --> 00:13:29,350
During my first year in prison...

119
00:13:31,894 --> 00:13:33,604
I wondered what I'd do to you

120
00:13:35,105 --> 00:13:36,565
once I got out...

121
00:13:38,734 --> 00:13:39,985
and how to pay you back.

122
00:13:42,321 --> 00:13:43,447
During the second year

123
00:13:44,990 --> 00:13:46,367
I kept thinking...

124
00:13:48,828 --> 00:13:50,037
"Why me, of all people?"

125
00:13:52,748 --> 00:13:54,625
After the third winter...

126
00:13:57,253 --> 00:13:59,755
I started thinking
about what could have driven you...

127
00:14:02,383 --> 00:14:04,051
to do something so horrific.

128
00:14:06,178 --> 00:14:07,513
And the year after that...

129
00:14:10,516 --> 00:14:12,518
I began taking pity on you.

130
00:14:15,479 --> 00:14:18,649
If you had had
even one proper adult in your life

131
00:14:20,192 --> 00:14:21,861
as a child

132
00:14:22,444 --> 00:14:26,740
I thought your path
might have been different.

133
00:14:28,450 --> 00:14:29,910
So, in the last year

134
00:14:32,079 --> 00:14:33,414
I decided to pray for you.

135
00:14:35,624 --> 00:14:37,042
And I started wondering

136
00:14:37,918 --> 00:14:41,797
if I could become
that one adult for you.

137
00:14:45,342 --> 00:14:46,969
Once I thought about it that way

138
00:14:48,721 --> 00:14:50,556
I stopped resenting you.

139
00:14:53,100 --> 00:14:54,643
So, don't carry any guilt.

140
00:14:56,604 --> 00:14:57,646
What happened then

141
00:14:59,106 --> 00:15:00,649
was simply my fate.

142
00:15:02,860 --> 00:15:04,361
That sounds just like you.

143
00:15:05,571 --> 00:15:07,156
I'm going to root for you.

144
00:15:07,698 --> 00:15:08,824
That's my way.

145
00:15:11,410 --> 00:15:15,831
So, live your life
remembering there's someone out there

146
00:15:16,498 --> 00:15:19,335
who genuinely pities you

147
00:15:21,629 --> 00:15:22,880
and sincerely cheers for you.

148
00:15:25,507 --> 00:15:26,800
Try living like that.

149
00:15:30,679 --> 00:15:32,598
That's the best revenge I can offer.

150
00:15:38,771 --> 00:15:41,106
But Mr. Choi.

151
00:15:46,070 --> 00:15:48,322
There's no such thing
as "best revenge."

152
00:15:50,115 --> 00:15:51,617
What just happened was

153
00:15:52,576 --> 00:15:54,578
that you missed
your one and only chance

154
00:15:55,621 --> 00:15:57,623
to take revenge on me.

155
00:16:03,045 --> 00:16:04,046
Thank you.

156
00:16:14,098 --> 00:16:15,641
HEO IN-GANG WAS KNOWN
TO BE DEEPLY AFFECTIONATE

157
00:16:15,724 --> 00:16:17,101
TOWARD HIS GRANDMOTHER...

158
00:16:17,184 --> 00:16:18,894
Baek Ah-jin and Heo In-gang?

159
00:16:19,353 --> 00:16:21,480
How long are you going to milk them?

160
00:16:21,563 --> 00:16:22,898
It works for the public.

161
00:16:23,440 --> 00:16:24,775
They're like a bone broth.

162
00:16:24,858 --> 00:16:27,277
You boil and boil,
and it still gives.

163
00:16:27,361 --> 00:16:30,239
It's about time
they broke up, though.

164
00:16:30,781 --> 00:16:33,075
I was going to lock in the breakup
as an exclusive

165
00:16:33,158 --> 00:16:34,660
and be done with it.

166
00:16:34,743 --> 00:16:36,829
Why split up a couple
that's doing fine?

167
00:16:36,912 --> 00:16:38,622
Isn't it obvious?

168
00:16:39,039 --> 00:16:41,542
Ah-jin is a rising sun,
and In-gang is a setting sun.

169
00:16:42,084 --> 00:16:45,754
She's gotten everything
she could out of him.

170
00:16:45,838 --> 00:16:48,424
Why would she keep dating him?

171
00:16:48,507 --> 00:16:50,300
Who knows?

172
00:16:50,384 --> 00:16:51,552
It could be true love.

173
00:16:54,847 --> 00:16:57,933
"True love"? You don't know anything.

174
00:17:26,211 --> 00:17:27,671
What do you want?

175
00:17:27,755 --> 00:17:29,006
Oh, nothing.

176
00:17:29,089 --> 00:17:32,801
I'm just calling to see
if there's anything new.

177
00:17:32,885 --> 00:17:36,597
Nothing pulls clicks
like you and In-gang.

178
00:17:37,056 --> 00:17:39,391
We're in mourning. Show some respect.

179
00:17:39,475 --> 00:17:41,143
I have something to verify--

180
00:17:41,226 --> 00:17:42,227
Hello?

181
00:17:42,644 --> 00:17:43,645
Hello...

182
00:17:46,023 --> 00:17:47,483
Right.

183
00:17:48,358 --> 00:17:50,277
For a time like this...

184
00:17:52,071 --> 00:17:53,072
RÉSUMÉ

185
00:17:53,155 --> 00:17:54,364
PHOTO

186
00:17:55,324 --> 00:17:57,159
Hello, Ms. Sim Sung-hee?

187
00:17:57,576 --> 00:17:59,286
I told you I never did that.

188
00:17:59,369 --> 00:18:01,914
It looks like Ah-jin's side
has already made a move.

189
00:18:01,997 --> 00:18:03,665
Was it Longstar's CEO, Seo Mi-ri?

190
00:18:04,124 --> 00:18:05,667
I don't know
what you're talking about.

191
00:18:06,877 --> 00:18:09,171
If you're going to keep talking
nonsense, I'm hanging up.

192
00:18:17,054 --> 00:18:18,680
I did what you told me to.

193
00:18:19,348 --> 00:18:20,599
Guess you're scared, after all.

194
00:18:24,269 --> 00:18:25,270
Figures.

195
00:18:25,646 --> 00:18:28,398
Your dad's past
as an adulterous lawyer

196
00:18:28,690 --> 00:18:31,151
and your own past,
stealing your classmates' stuff

197
00:18:31,235 --> 00:18:33,028
beaten by the homeroom teacher
and kids

198
00:18:33,112 --> 00:18:34,655
and forced to transfer.

199
00:18:35,906 --> 00:18:38,200
It'll look bad on you
if those spread in your workplace.

200
00:18:41,036 --> 00:18:43,539
You saw the comments
on your post last time, right?

201
00:18:44,832 --> 00:18:46,667
Plenty of people still remember you.

202
00:18:47,459 --> 00:18:50,003
So, unless you want
your past dragged out in the open

203
00:18:50,087 --> 00:18:51,588
shut your mouth and lie low.

204
00:18:55,134 --> 00:18:56,135
If not

205
00:18:57,427 --> 00:18:59,972
I'll follow you around
with your past everywhere you go.

206
00:19:11,483 --> 00:19:12,484
Fuck.

207
00:19:12,568 --> 00:19:15,863
SAMYUN SEOUL HOSPITAL MEMORIAL HALL

208
00:19:18,907 --> 00:19:19,908
Director.

209
00:19:22,077 --> 00:19:23,078
Hello.

210
00:19:25,247 --> 00:19:26,665
Are you heading out now?

211
00:19:27,082 --> 00:19:28,667
Oh, Ms. Baek Ah-jin.

212
00:19:29,793 --> 00:19:31,503
I'm glad you know my name.

213
00:19:31,587 --> 00:19:33,338
I was nervous you might not.

214
00:19:33,589 --> 00:19:36,091
Of course, I do.
I enjoyed your works.

215
00:19:36,633 --> 00:19:37,634
Thank you.

216
00:19:38,552 --> 00:19:40,804
I've watched all of yours as well.

217
00:19:41,054 --> 00:19:42,681
I'm a big fan.

218
00:19:42,764 --> 00:19:44,892
And In-gang talks about you so much.

219
00:19:44,975 --> 00:19:48,353
He does?
I should buy him a meal sometime.

220
00:19:48,437 --> 00:19:49,438
No need.

221
00:19:49,938 --> 00:19:51,815
Since you came today

222
00:19:51,899 --> 00:19:57,654
once he settles down,
let me treat you to a meal with him.

223
00:19:59,072 --> 00:20:00,282
What do you say?

224
00:20:00,532 --> 00:20:02,409
I'd love that. Anytime.

225
00:20:03,118 --> 00:20:04,953
For today, please stay by him

226
00:20:05,537 --> 00:20:06,955
and comfort him.

227
00:20:07,789 --> 00:20:08,790
I will.

228
00:20:10,667 --> 00:20:12,753
- Get home safe.
- Thanks.

229
00:20:16,423 --> 00:20:17,507
Ms. Baek.

230
00:20:19,343 --> 00:20:21,053
If you don't mind

231
00:20:21,136 --> 00:20:23,639
how about you drop
by my studio sometime?

232
00:20:27,726 --> 00:20:30,604
He must have seen Ah-jin
at In-gang's grandma's funeral.

233
00:20:30,854 --> 00:20:32,606
He said she was the image
he'd been looking for

234
00:20:32,689 --> 00:20:36,985
and wants her to play
a key role in his new work.

235
00:20:37,486 --> 00:20:39,279
Director Seol Yeong-uk is...

236
00:20:39,363 --> 00:20:41,156
It'll be invited
to the Cannes Film Festival

237
00:20:41,240 --> 00:20:43,784
and that naturally opens
a route into the global market.

238
00:20:43,867 --> 00:20:46,161
There's no better opportunity
for an actor.

239
00:20:46,245 --> 00:20:48,413
It's what every actor dreams of.

240
00:20:51,583 --> 00:20:55,045
In-gang's grandma left Ah-jin
a big gift as she passed.

241
00:21:13,981 --> 00:21:15,399
You're curious, aren't you?

242
00:21:16,275 --> 00:21:19,403
Whether I was the one
who did it to her that night.

243
00:21:27,119 --> 00:21:28,495
What do you think?

244
00:21:30,038 --> 00:21:32,040
Do you think I could go that far?

245
00:21:37,004 --> 00:21:38,171
I don't get you.

246
00:21:42,509 --> 00:21:44,094
It must have been hard

247
00:21:44,344 --> 00:21:46,888
thinking about what to do with a girl
who even committed a murder.

248
00:21:48,223 --> 00:21:49,224
Say it.

249
00:21:51,727 --> 00:21:53,145
It wasn't you, right?

250
00:21:53,228 --> 00:21:55,689
And what happens if it were me?

251
00:22:01,361 --> 00:22:02,446
You're right.

252
00:22:04,114 --> 00:22:05,782
She started getting on my nerves.

253
00:22:06,783 --> 00:22:08,660
She was no use to me anymore

254
00:22:09,369 --> 00:22:11,079
and constantly got in my way.

255
00:22:12,998 --> 00:22:15,792
She had also found out
that I approached her on purpose.

256
00:22:19,796 --> 00:22:23,425
So, what do you think I did to her?

257
00:22:25,052 --> 00:22:26,053
Is that true?

258
00:22:26,511 --> 00:22:27,804
Did you really do it?

259
00:22:29,264 --> 00:22:30,974
Whatever you're thinking
is the truth.

260
00:22:31,058 --> 00:22:32,059
Baek Ah-jin.

261
00:22:38,565 --> 00:22:40,108
This is so exhausting.

262
00:23:33,578 --> 00:23:35,414
Excuse me.

263
00:23:35,831 --> 00:23:38,583
You're the grandson of the lady
who lived in Unit 401, right?

264
00:23:42,170 --> 00:23:44,005
My grandma was crying?

265
00:23:44,589 --> 00:23:48,093
Yes, she was practically wailing,
so I was shocked.

266
00:23:48,176 --> 00:23:49,636
She normally doesn't do that.

267
00:23:50,137 --> 00:23:52,097
By the time she calmed down

268
00:23:52,180 --> 00:23:54,933
a pretty, young woman
walked into her place.

269
00:23:55,225 --> 00:23:58,311
I brought her some red bean porridge

270
00:23:58,562 --> 00:24:00,689
and saw something strange
at the door.

271
00:24:01,982 --> 00:24:03,066
What was it?

272
00:24:03,150 --> 00:24:06,570
Your grandma was pounding
the young woman's chest

273
00:24:06,987 --> 00:24:11,199
saying things like, "I trusted you
who deceived my whole family."

274
00:24:11,283 --> 00:24:13,368
It was something like that.

275
00:24:15,912 --> 00:24:19,374
Also, the woman in Unit 409 said

276
00:24:19,458 --> 00:24:21,334
someone kept stealing her packages

277
00:24:21,418 --> 00:24:24,296
so she secretly set up
a camera in the hallway.

278
00:24:25,255 --> 00:24:27,799
But it's illegal

279
00:24:27,883 --> 00:24:30,177
so she probably didn't tell
the police.

280
00:24:30,260 --> 00:24:32,596
But if your grandma fell
down the stairs

281
00:24:32,679 --> 00:24:34,389
between the fourth and third floors

282
00:24:34,473 --> 00:24:36,516
it might have been filmed.

283
00:24:38,977 --> 00:24:42,022
Could I speak with her?

284
00:24:42,731 --> 00:24:45,775
My husband saved
a copy of the footage just in case

285
00:24:45,859 --> 00:24:47,527
but a detective came and got it.

286
00:24:48,069 --> 00:24:49,696
I see.

287
00:24:50,530 --> 00:24:51,573
Thank you.

288
00:25:10,133 --> 00:25:11,760
Don't ever make me do
stuff like this again.

289
00:25:12,427 --> 00:25:15,096
You, of all people,
should believe in Ah-jin, damn it.

290
00:25:17,140 --> 00:25:18,767
- Did you see it?
- No.

291
00:25:19,392 --> 00:25:20,435
I don't need to.

292
00:25:20,894 --> 00:25:22,437
I believe her. She's innocent.

293
00:25:32,364 --> 00:25:33,782
And don't worry about Sung-hee.

294
00:25:34,366 --> 00:25:36,826
I gave her a good scare, so she won't
dare open her mouth again.

295
00:25:36,910 --> 00:25:38,453
She won't be spreading stories
about Ah-jin.

296
00:25:39,287 --> 00:25:40,288
Good.

297
00:26:08,483 --> 00:26:10,819
In-gang, are you still in bed?

298
00:26:10,902 --> 00:26:12,153
Yes, why?

299
00:26:12,612 --> 00:26:14,531
Come on. You too?

300
00:26:15,532 --> 00:26:17,784
I heard you backed out of the film
you were supposed to do.

301
00:26:18,618 --> 00:26:20,912
We've got to hang in there
now more than ever.

302
00:26:21,580 --> 00:26:23,039
Don't keep starving yourself.

303
00:26:23,790 --> 00:26:25,250
Remember to eat.

304
00:26:26,459 --> 00:26:28,295
Ah-jin brought me some porridge.

305
00:26:29,462 --> 00:26:30,589
I'll have it later.

306
00:26:49,274 --> 00:26:51,818
I saw you were asleep, so I left.

307
00:26:51,901 --> 00:26:53,778
Don't skip meals, okay?

308
00:26:54,487 --> 00:26:55,530
I love you.

309
00:26:59,868 --> 00:27:01,202
HEO IN-GANG SPOTTED
SHOPPING FOR RINGS IN HONG KONG

310
00:27:02,078 --> 00:27:05,165
There are headlines saying
you're about to get married now.

311
00:27:05,248 --> 00:27:07,042
This is a problem, Ms. Baek.

312
00:27:07,292 --> 00:27:09,002
You do know

313
00:27:09,085 --> 00:27:11,338
what kind of character
you're playing, right?

314
00:27:11,421 --> 00:27:14,424
If audiences can't stay
immersed in my film

315
00:27:14,507 --> 00:27:17,802
because of your real-life romance
or marriage rumors

316
00:27:17,886 --> 00:27:20,096
I've got no reason to cast you, do I?

317
00:27:21,556 --> 00:27:22,557
I'm sorry.

318
00:27:23,266 --> 00:27:25,894
I wasn't expecting
this kind of speculation, either.

319
00:27:29,898 --> 00:27:33,485
I actually like
seeing you and In-gang together.

320
00:27:33,568 --> 00:27:37,739
I got to work with you thanks to him,
and I appreciate that.

321
00:27:37,822 --> 00:27:40,575
But let's keep personal
and professional matters separate.

322
00:27:40,659 --> 00:27:42,619
You're not dumb enough
to confuse them

323
00:27:43,453 --> 00:27:44,454
right?

324
00:27:45,622 --> 00:27:46,623
No, Director.

325
00:27:48,208 --> 00:27:50,043
Director, you're already here!

326
00:27:50,126 --> 00:27:51,586
I came as early as I could.

327
00:27:52,587 --> 00:27:54,339
Long time no see, Ms. Seo.

328
00:27:54,631 --> 00:27:55,632
Hi.

329
00:27:57,592 --> 00:28:00,345
I don't see Mr. Yoon, though.
Is he running late?

330
00:28:01,179 --> 00:28:04,349
He said
we should meet on a better day.

331
00:28:05,058 --> 00:28:07,560
He said today wasn't
the night for drinking.

332
00:28:08,687 --> 00:28:12,607
Anyway, I'll get going.
Let's talk again soon.

333
00:28:13,358 --> 00:28:14,484
Of course.

334
00:28:14,859 --> 00:28:16,069
We'll see you soon.

335
00:28:16,569 --> 00:28:17,779
Take care!

336
00:28:24,828 --> 00:28:27,038
It must have been tough
cleaning up the mess.

337
00:28:28,123 --> 00:28:30,834
I only posted a statement asking
to refrain from wild speculations.

338
00:28:31,459 --> 00:28:32,502
What about In-gang?

339
00:28:33,586 --> 00:28:35,922
When has he ever cared
about articles?

340
00:28:36,381 --> 00:28:38,925
His fans are already freaking out
that he can't get married yet.

341
00:28:39,592 --> 00:28:41,469
But he's talking about retiring
once his contract's over.

342
00:28:41,553 --> 00:28:42,971
It's driving me insane.

343
00:28:46,015 --> 00:28:47,934
He really said that?

344
00:28:49,728 --> 00:28:51,146
He didn't tell you?

345
00:28:51,646 --> 00:28:53,606
I had my phone turned off.

346
00:28:54,566 --> 00:28:56,818
It was getting too chaotic
due to all the calls coming in.

347
00:29:00,822 --> 00:29:03,533
You didn't know
about the ring, either, did you?

348
00:29:05,118 --> 00:29:06,119
No.

349
00:29:07,996 --> 00:29:10,039
Are you going to marry him?

350
00:29:15,295 --> 00:29:17,297
No, I'm going to end it.

351
00:29:18,506 --> 00:29:19,883
You'll back me up, right?

352
00:29:22,343 --> 00:29:23,344
Ah-jin.

353
00:29:23,970 --> 00:29:25,638
While preparing for your birthday

354
00:29:26,806 --> 00:29:28,808
I realized

355
00:29:28,892 --> 00:29:31,227
it was the first time in my life
I had ever felt so deeply grateful

356
00:29:31,895 --> 00:29:33,021
that someone was born.

357
00:29:34,189 --> 00:29:39,277
I suddenly understood how huge
my feelings for you had become.

358
00:29:40,695 --> 00:29:41,946
This must be love.

359
00:29:43,740 --> 00:29:45,700
Let's share our lives together.

360
00:29:47,243 --> 00:29:49,996
Let's fill and exchange our love

361
00:29:50,830 --> 00:29:52,040
within the same everyday life.

362
00:29:53,500 --> 00:29:54,793
I want to marry you.

363
00:29:56,377 --> 00:29:57,504
You're home, right?

364
00:30:09,891 --> 00:30:12,185
I'll be at your place in ten minutes.

365
00:30:12,727 --> 00:30:13,728
We need to talk.

366
00:30:17,482 --> 00:30:19,400
Will you stay by my side?

367
00:30:39,295 --> 00:30:40,505
What are you hesitating about?

368
00:30:40,880 --> 00:30:42,173
Is it something exciting?

369
00:30:43,508 --> 00:30:44,592
Something scary.

370
00:30:44,843 --> 00:30:46,761
I'm not sure if I can handle it.

371
00:30:46,845 --> 00:30:47,887
Scary?

372
00:30:48,263 --> 00:30:49,264
Like what?

373
00:30:50,056 --> 00:30:51,266
It's just scary.

374
00:30:53,768 --> 00:30:55,353
Then throw it away.

375
00:30:55,436 --> 00:30:56,646
I wish I could.

376
00:31:02,902 --> 00:31:05,113
Why isn't he home yet?

377
00:31:08,718 --> 00:31:16,718
Officail Website : kissasian.be  Translate by =Qari= @Team Viki

378
00:31:10,743 --> 00:31:11,870
Man.

379
00:31:13,496 --> 00:31:14,497
What are you doing?

380
00:31:15,665 --> 00:31:17,208
Wait, who are you?

381
00:31:17,917 --> 00:31:18,918
"Who are you?"

382
00:31:19,002 --> 00:31:20,003
Are you serious?

383
00:31:20,545 --> 00:31:22,964
Don't you even remember the guy
you hugged last time?

384
00:31:24,883 --> 00:31:26,175
Go make some ramyeon.

385
00:31:26,801 --> 00:31:27,802
I'm sorry?

386
00:31:29,888 --> 00:31:31,681
It's for Jun-seo's stomach.

387
00:31:32,473 --> 00:31:34,767
He needs something spicy to sober up.

388
00:31:38,104 --> 00:31:39,647
Jackass.

389
00:31:59,167 --> 00:32:00,168
Gosh.

390
00:32:24,943 --> 00:32:27,403
I was worried
something had happened to you.

391
00:32:29,238 --> 00:32:30,865
It relieves me to see your face.

392
00:32:34,577 --> 00:32:37,789
In-gang,
are you thinking of retiring?

393
00:32:40,416 --> 00:32:41,668
Did Mi-ri tell you?

394
00:32:43,252 --> 00:32:45,630
Why didn't you tell me first?

395
00:32:46,547 --> 00:32:48,174
I didn't mean to hide it.

396
00:32:49,050 --> 00:32:51,302
It wasn't easy to make up my mind.

397
00:32:51,678 --> 00:32:54,555
I was going to tell you
once I was sure.

398
00:33:03,064 --> 00:33:07,276
Are you planning to marry me
after you retire?

399
00:33:12,156 --> 00:33:13,908
I thought we were on the same page.

400
00:33:15,952 --> 00:33:17,078
Was I wrong?

401
00:33:18,913 --> 00:33:21,624
Then you shouldn't have let it
become news.

402
00:33:22,250 --> 00:33:23,292
What?

403
00:33:26,754 --> 00:33:28,715
I feel awful.

404
00:33:30,466 --> 00:33:31,592
Do you have any idea

405
00:33:31,676 --> 00:33:33,553
how humiliated I was
in front of the director today?

406
00:33:35,054 --> 00:33:36,472
Why should I have to take

407
00:33:37,140 --> 00:33:38,683
that kind of criticism
because of you?

408
00:33:41,060 --> 00:33:42,061
Ah-jin.

409
00:33:47,191 --> 00:33:48,568
Let me ask you one favor.

410
00:33:50,236 --> 00:33:53,656
You're a good guy who always
does me a favor when I ask

411
00:33:53,906 --> 00:33:56,200
so I hope you do it again this time.

412
00:34:00,496 --> 00:34:02,373
Let's break up.

413
00:34:11,466 --> 00:34:12,717
Hang on.

414
00:34:13,384 --> 00:34:15,303
What kind of nonsense is this?

415
00:34:15,386 --> 00:34:17,221
This is too sudden.

416
00:34:18,473 --> 00:34:19,932
I know you're angry, but...

417
00:34:21,768 --> 00:34:23,644
Are you even the same Ah-jin I know?

418
00:34:23,728 --> 00:34:27,231
And are you the In-gang I know?

419
00:34:28,524 --> 00:34:30,401
You're not in your right mind.

420
00:34:31,152 --> 00:34:32,820
You can't even control your emotions

421
00:34:32,904 --> 00:34:34,989
babbling about retiring
and fairy-tale dreams.

422
00:34:35,073 --> 00:34:36,783
Get a grip.

423
00:34:37,617 --> 00:34:41,537
Do you know how many fans you've lost
in the year we've been together?

424
00:34:41,788 --> 00:34:43,998
And now you want me to marry you?

425
00:34:46,250 --> 00:34:48,961
Don't make me laugh.
And what about me?

426
00:34:50,296 --> 00:34:52,507
You want to put
a "married woman" label on me

427
00:34:52,590 --> 00:34:55,843
while I lose my movie roles,
so I can watch as my career dies?

428
00:34:57,845 --> 00:35:01,516
How can a person change
so completely overnight?

429
00:35:02,767 --> 00:35:03,768
Why?

430
00:35:06,521 --> 00:35:08,314
You don't like the new me?

431
00:35:09,732 --> 00:35:12,777
Then would you rather have me
smile sweetly

432
00:35:14,153 --> 00:35:15,696
while I break up with you?

433
00:35:17,532 --> 00:35:19,242
Would that make it easier for you?

434
00:35:24,497 --> 00:35:25,957
We've been together a year.

435
00:35:27,875 --> 00:35:31,087
I thought I knew you,
and I was certain about us.

436
00:35:32,588 --> 00:35:34,715
That's why I pictured
a future together.

437
00:35:35,842 --> 00:35:37,301
Was that so wrong?

438
00:35:38,094 --> 00:35:40,096
You know how much pain
I'm in right now.

439
00:35:41,472 --> 00:35:42,640
Can't you even try to understand--

440
00:35:42,723 --> 00:35:45,059
Why should I understand you?

441
00:35:46,394 --> 00:35:48,312
It wasn't ten years,
not even five years.

442
00:35:48,396 --> 00:35:51,232
Who cares
about a one-year relationship?

443
00:35:51,858 --> 00:35:54,402
You thought I knew you? Well, I...

444
00:35:56,863 --> 00:35:59,365
I've never heard
such an arrogant thing in my life.

445
00:36:04,287 --> 00:36:05,955
I can't believe this.

446
00:36:08,040 --> 00:36:09,667
I wish this were a dream.

447
00:36:11,252 --> 00:36:13,129
Given your tragic life

448
00:36:13,212 --> 00:36:14,922
I'm probably not
even nightmare-worthy.

449
00:36:17,216 --> 00:36:20,136
Don't make a scene over something
as ordinary as a breakup.

450
00:36:27,143 --> 00:36:28,352
Ah-jin, what's wrong?

451
00:36:28,436 --> 00:36:29,478
Come on.

452
00:36:31,564 --> 00:36:33,399
- Don't do this.
- In-gang.

453
00:36:36,736 --> 00:36:37,862
What I'm about to say

454
00:36:39,030 --> 00:36:40,239
will hurt.

455
00:36:47,705 --> 00:36:49,332
I'm already hurting.

456
00:36:52,960 --> 00:36:54,503
You were pretending ignorance.

457
00:37:10,269 --> 00:37:11,395
But listen anyway.

458
00:37:12,772 --> 00:37:13,940
Don't try to avoid it.

459
00:37:19,946 --> 00:37:21,155
Your grandma's notebook.

460
00:37:23,616 --> 00:37:24,909
I stole it.

461
00:37:28,329 --> 00:37:31,707
I wanted to win her favor
so I could date you.

462
00:37:33,793 --> 00:37:37,046
She found it at my place a while ago

463
00:37:38,256 --> 00:37:39,465
and she found out...

464
00:37:41,300 --> 00:37:42,677
what kind of person I am.

465
00:37:44,929 --> 00:37:46,055
And from that shock

466
00:37:47,306 --> 00:37:48,307
she...

467
00:37:53,020 --> 00:37:54,730
You understand what I mean, right?

468
00:38:01,988 --> 00:38:02,989
In-gang.

469
00:38:05,283 --> 00:38:06,284
How you fell

470
00:38:08,244 --> 00:38:10,204
in love with me...

471
00:38:12,623 --> 00:38:14,292
and what happened to your grandma--

472
00:38:14,375 --> 00:38:15,668
What the hell did you do?

473
00:38:18,129 --> 00:38:19,130
All I did was...

474
00:38:21,882 --> 00:38:23,843
tell her the truth.

475
00:38:26,304 --> 00:38:28,973
I asked what you did to my grandma!

476
00:38:35,646 --> 00:38:37,398
I simply told her honestly.

477
00:38:38,858 --> 00:38:41,527
For once in my life.

478
00:39:00,504 --> 00:39:01,672
Say that again.

479
00:39:06,093 --> 00:39:07,595
If you don't let go of me now

480
00:39:08,512 --> 00:39:11,098
you'll be in hell
every time you think of her.

481
00:39:12,308 --> 00:39:14,852
You're not the type of person
who can handle that.

482
00:39:18,356 --> 00:39:19,440
So, admit it.

483
00:39:20,733 --> 00:39:22,902
Our ending was already decided.

484
00:39:27,073 --> 00:39:28,949
I'll release the breakup article

485
00:39:29,033 --> 00:39:32,411
through a reporter I know
at the right time.

486
00:39:33,287 --> 00:39:38,292
The reason will be
"grew apart due to busy schedules."

487
00:39:39,794 --> 00:39:41,128
About Ms. Seo...

488
00:39:43,672 --> 00:39:45,633
I'll tell her myself,
so get some rest for now.

489
00:39:47,426 --> 00:39:49,553
You look like you haven't slept
since your grandma passed.

490
00:39:52,807 --> 00:39:53,808
Get a good sleep.

491
00:40:40,521 --> 00:40:42,064
It's me, Mr. Lim.

492
00:40:42,148 --> 00:40:44,024
What is it, at this hour?

493
00:40:44,108 --> 00:40:46,527
I think it's time to end
our little arrangement.

494
00:40:47,236 --> 00:40:48,237
What?

495
00:40:48,487 --> 00:40:50,614
Don't tell me
you're going to marry In-gang.

496
00:40:50,698 --> 00:40:52,074
No, it's the opposite.

497
00:40:52,158 --> 00:40:53,159
The opposite?

498
00:40:53,242 --> 00:40:55,494
Get a breakup article ready for us.

499
00:40:55,578 --> 00:40:57,288
Breakup? Hold on.

500
00:40:57,371 --> 00:41:00,416
Just write we drifted apart
due to our busy schedules.

501
00:41:00,499 --> 00:41:03,210
- You're seriously going through--
- As quickly as possible, please.

502
00:41:06,046 --> 00:41:08,924
CEO SEO MI-RI

503
00:41:21,270 --> 00:41:22,313
Hey, Boss.

504
00:41:22,396 --> 00:41:23,397
Where are you?

505
00:41:38,829 --> 00:41:41,040
Boss, don't pull over.
Just keep driving.

506
00:41:41,123 --> 00:41:42,416
You've got a tail behind you.

507
00:42:18,869 --> 00:42:20,079
Who are you?

508
00:42:20,371 --> 00:42:22,248
Are you a stalker?

509
00:42:22,540 --> 00:42:23,541
Or gangsters?

510
00:42:24,083 --> 00:42:25,960
You've got nothing better
to do with your lives?

511
00:42:27,586 --> 00:42:28,587
Get out.

512
00:42:49,316 --> 00:42:50,317
Get him.

513
00:42:51,026 --> 00:42:52,736
- No!
- Punk.

514
00:43:12,840 --> 00:43:13,882
Let's stop all this.

515
00:43:14,133 --> 00:43:16,010
Forget about Ah-jin now.

516
00:43:29,398 --> 00:43:31,567
She's not the right girl for you.

517
00:43:31,650 --> 00:43:33,110
We won't renew her contract, either.

518
00:43:33,902 --> 00:43:35,070
I know.

519
00:43:37,197 --> 00:43:40,075
All lovers break up in the end.

520
00:43:43,245 --> 00:43:45,205
This kind of breakup happens
to everybody.

521
00:43:47,708 --> 00:43:48,959
Just today.

522
00:43:50,669 --> 00:43:52,880
I'll let it hurt just for today.

523
00:43:58,636 --> 00:43:59,845
Just for today?

524
00:44:07,645 --> 00:44:09,980
Fine. Let's drink, then.

525
00:44:13,859 --> 00:44:15,611
Let's get totally wasted tonight.

526
00:44:19,740 --> 00:44:21,367
It brings back old memories.

527
00:44:27,414 --> 00:44:28,457
Thanks, Mi-ri.

528
00:44:30,000 --> 00:44:31,001
For what?

529
00:44:35,881 --> 00:44:36,882
Thank you.

530
00:44:40,177 --> 00:44:41,178
Silly.

531
00:44:41,762 --> 00:44:43,180
Pour me some more. Is this a joke?

532
00:45:09,248 --> 00:45:10,249
AH-JIN

533
00:45:22,636 --> 00:45:23,846
Hey, Ah-jin.

534
00:45:24,346 --> 00:45:26,849
Jae-oh, who was in that car
that was following me?

535
00:45:29,309 --> 00:45:30,310
Paparazzi.

536
00:45:31,562 --> 00:45:33,439
I talked to them and sent them away

537
00:45:34,189 --> 00:45:35,190
so don't worry.

538
00:45:37,526 --> 00:45:40,070
You didn't call me out
for something urgent, right?

539
00:45:40,904 --> 00:45:44,283
No, I'm a little tired today.
I'll talk to you later.

540
00:45:46,493 --> 00:45:47,870
I'll call you.

541
00:46:25,240 --> 00:46:26,325
What?

542
00:46:26,408 --> 00:46:28,035
HEO IN-GANG AND BAEK AH-JIN
BREAK UP AFTER 1 YEAR

543
00:46:28,118 --> 00:46:29,411
GREW DISTANT DUE TO BUSY SCHEDULES

544
00:46:29,495 --> 00:46:30,996
THE FAMOUS COUPLE
HEO IN-GANG AND BAEK AH-JIN

545
00:46:31,079 --> 00:46:32,623
ENDED THEIR RELATIONSHIP
AFTER A TURBULENT YEAR

546
00:46:40,589 --> 00:46:42,257
Ms. Seo, these documents are for you.

547
00:46:43,175 --> 00:46:45,010
Yes, fix the parts I marked.

548
00:46:46,261 --> 00:46:47,346
Where's In-gang?

549
00:46:47,596 --> 00:46:48,847
His manager called and said

550
00:46:48,931 --> 00:46:50,849
he just went to bed
after taking sleeping pills.

551
00:46:52,476 --> 00:46:54,311
He won't be up
until late afternoon, then.

552
00:46:54,895 --> 00:46:56,104
That brat probably skipped food

553
00:46:56,188 --> 00:46:57,731
and poured alcohol
into an empty stomach.

554
00:47:00,025 --> 00:47:02,194
Is there
a good hangover-soup place nearby?

555
00:47:02,945 --> 00:47:04,446
Are you taking it to him?

556
00:47:04,530 --> 00:47:06,573
I'll swing by his place
on my way home.

557
00:47:07,366 --> 00:47:10,953
I need to make him eat something
and pull himself together.

558
00:47:43,569 --> 00:47:45,487
I'm out of town right now

559
00:47:45,571 --> 00:47:47,239
but In-gang isn't picking up
the phone.

560
00:47:47,698 --> 00:47:50,075
He's just passed out
from drinking too much.

561
00:47:50,158 --> 00:47:51,660
I'm heading over
with hangover soup now.

562
00:47:51,743 --> 00:47:54,329
I'll feed him
and tell him to call you.

563
00:47:54,413 --> 00:47:55,414
Yes.

564
00:47:55,497 --> 00:47:57,165
Don't worry, In-mo.
Focus on your work.

565
00:47:57,249 --> 00:47:58,375
Okay.

566
00:48:21,481 --> 00:48:24,067
In-gang, wake up!
Time to fix that hangover.

567
00:48:25,277 --> 00:48:29,156
I brought you
some amazing hangover soup.

568
00:48:36,079 --> 00:48:38,373
He's still asleep, huh?

569
00:48:40,626 --> 00:48:41,835
In-gang!

570
00:48:45,589 --> 00:48:47,591
Where is he?

571
00:50:24,896 --> 00:50:25,897
In-gang.

572
00:50:27,983 --> 00:50:29,317
In-gang, no.

573
00:50:31,445 --> 00:50:33,572
No!

574
00:50:34,990 --> 00:50:37,409
No!

575
00:51:15,113 --> 00:51:16,114
Hey.

576
00:51:16,948 --> 00:51:18,241
Look at me.

577
00:51:19,284 --> 00:51:20,285
Ridiculous, right?

578
00:51:25,373 --> 00:51:26,374
What happened?

579
00:51:26,958 --> 00:51:28,376
You've never been this hurt.

580
00:51:28,877 --> 00:51:30,003
What have you been doing?

581
00:51:32,380 --> 00:51:35,217
I just got unlucky.

582
00:51:37,219 --> 00:51:38,220
How's Boss?

583
00:51:39,554 --> 00:51:40,555
What?

584
00:51:40,972 --> 00:51:42,015
Is she all right?

585
00:51:42,516 --> 00:51:43,642
Why are you asking that?

586
00:51:46,228 --> 00:51:47,938
As long as nothing happened to her.

587
00:51:59,533 --> 00:52:01,243
Who the hell were those guys, anyway?

588
00:52:01,326 --> 00:52:02,869
Heo In-gang is dead.

589
00:52:04,121 --> 00:52:05,497
Seriously? Was it suicide?

590
00:52:05,997 --> 00:52:08,250
But he recently broke up
with Baek Ah-jin.

591
00:52:08,333 --> 00:52:11,253
Wait, does that mean
he killed himself because of her?

592
00:52:11,336 --> 00:52:12,712
That can't be.

593
00:52:12,796 --> 00:52:14,089
Apparently, he had depression.

594
00:52:49,416 --> 00:52:51,251
What did you say to me before?

595
00:52:51,501 --> 00:52:53,295
What did you say to me last time?

596
00:52:55,130 --> 00:52:57,591
You said you were just going to have
a normal relationship and break up.

597
00:52:57,674 --> 00:53:00,093
You said yourself
that he wouldn't get hurt.

598
00:53:00,886 --> 00:53:02,137
You're hilarious.

599
00:53:02,762 --> 00:53:03,763
Why are you angry?

600
00:53:05,390 --> 00:53:07,184
Who are you to yell at me?

601
00:53:09,019 --> 00:53:11,229
He couldn't accept the breakup.
That's on him.

602
00:53:11,313 --> 00:53:12,981
I did everything I could.

603
00:53:13,607 --> 00:53:15,025
How is that my fault?

604
00:53:15,692 --> 00:53:18,820
It was bad luck on his part
that he ended up like that.

605
00:53:20,530 --> 00:53:21,948
That's not my fault.

606
00:53:27,204 --> 00:53:28,580
He's dead.

607
00:53:30,040 --> 00:53:32,584
An entire family was shattered
in an instant.

608
00:53:35,212 --> 00:53:36,630
And that's all you have to say?

609
00:53:37,714 --> 00:53:40,300
You make it sound like I killed him.

610
00:53:40,383 --> 00:53:41,426
Didn't you?

611
00:53:43,595 --> 00:53:46,389
Did you think I'd feel guilty?

612
00:53:46,473 --> 00:53:48,058
Don't expect that from me.

613
00:53:48,642 --> 00:53:50,518
You're the only one
who'll end up hurt and disappointed.

614
00:53:56,858 --> 00:53:57,901
Can't you just...

615
00:53:59,736 --> 00:54:01,446
live like a normal person?

616
00:54:06,910 --> 00:54:08,870
It was my mistake
for thinking you had

617
00:54:08,954 --> 00:54:10,789
even a shred of humanity in you.

618
00:54:12,374 --> 00:54:14,626
How exactly
am I supposed to be human?

619
00:54:15,502 --> 00:54:18,255
Do you think things would have
turned out differently

620
00:54:18,338 --> 00:54:20,257
if you had pulled me
out of that bathtub?

621
00:54:21,299 --> 00:54:23,009
But you didn't.

622
00:54:23,093 --> 00:54:25,428
Jae-oh would have stormed
into the bathroom

623
00:54:25,512 --> 00:54:28,223
and smashed that woman's head,
but you didn't.

624
00:54:28,765 --> 00:54:31,017
And you dare to judge me?

625
00:54:34,854 --> 00:54:38,149
Did you just stand there and watch
because you had humanity?

626
00:54:40,193 --> 00:54:41,945
This isn't my fault.

627
00:54:42,988 --> 00:54:44,823
You made me like this.

628
00:54:47,534 --> 00:54:50,537
If you feel bad for me,
say you're sorry.

629
00:54:51,621 --> 00:54:54,291
Say you're sorry
you turned me into this.

630
00:54:55,792 --> 00:54:57,377
When you condemn me

631
00:54:57,460 --> 00:54:59,170
you're actually condemning
your past self.

632
00:55:09,347 --> 00:55:11,224
You can blame me all you want

633
00:55:12,642 --> 00:55:14,269
but I'll never blame you.

634
00:55:24,070 --> 00:55:26,990
If you want to leave me, then do it.

635
00:55:31,411 --> 00:55:33,455
Run away from me

636
00:55:33,955 --> 00:55:35,582
just like you did in the past...

637
00:55:37,625 --> 00:55:39,961
and I still won't blame you.

638
00:55:46,092 --> 00:55:49,012
Because you're the first person
I chose to keep by my side.

639
00:56:29,719 --> 00:56:32,806
I was afraid my grandma
wouldn't be able to get her surgery.

640
00:56:33,765 --> 00:56:35,392
Thank you, Manager.

641
00:56:36,059 --> 00:56:37,519
I'll never forget this.

642
00:56:37,602 --> 00:56:39,229
I'm not a manager anymore.

643
00:56:39,312 --> 00:56:41,856
You can call me CEO now.

644
00:56:41,940 --> 00:56:43,066
And just so you know

645
00:56:43,149 --> 00:56:45,276
I never forget
a favor I gave, either.

646
00:56:45,360 --> 00:56:46,569
Thank you, truly.

647
00:56:49,114 --> 00:56:50,115
Hello.

648
00:56:55,745 --> 00:56:57,497
You said you never forget
a favor you've done.

649
00:56:57,747 --> 00:56:59,416
I wish you massive success, Ms. Seo.

650
00:57:01,042 --> 00:57:02,335
Thank you.

651
00:57:03,920 --> 00:57:06,131
REPRESENTATIVE: SEO MI-RI
NAME: HEO IN-GANG

652
00:57:09,801 --> 00:57:11,719
I never forget
the favors I receive, either.

653
00:57:12,137 --> 00:57:13,680
I sure know
how to pick the right people.

654
00:57:21,980 --> 00:57:25,191
I just want to thank you.

655
00:57:40,582 --> 00:57:43,168
HEO IN-GANG

656
00:58:54,489 --> 00:58:56,241
Everyone ends up abandoned

657
00:58:56,908 --> 00:58:58,159
and broken in life.

658
00:58:59,452 --> 00:59:01,329
You were just too weak.

659
00:59:12,674 --> 00:59:14,842
I couldn't just fall apart with you.

660
00:59:25,061 --> 00:59:26,437
Please understand me.

661
00:59:59,012 --> 01:00:00,847
- Kick her out!
- Kick her out!

662
01:00:00,930 --> 01:00:02,515
Kick Baek Ah-jin out!

663
01:00:02,599 --> 01:00:04,350
- Kick her out!
- Kick her out!

664
01:00:04,434 --> 01:00:05,852
This is unfair!

665
01:00:05,935 --> 01:00:07,729
- Unfair!
- Unfair!

666
01:00:07,812 --> 01:00:09,606
Take responsibility, Longstar!

667
01:00:09,689 --> 01:00:11,524
- Take responsibility!
- Take responsibility!

668
01:00:11,608 --> 01:00:13,234
This is unfair!

669
01:00:13,318 --> 01:00:15,236
- Unfair!
- Unfair!

670
01:00:15,320 --> 01:00:17,113
Baek Ah-jin is a criminal!

671
01:00:17,196 --> 01:00:19,073
- Criminal!
- Criminal!

672
01:00:19,157 --> 01:00:20,867
Kick Baek Ah-jin out!

673
01:00:20,950 --> 01:00:22,869
- Kick her out!
- Kick her out!

674
01:00:22,952 --> 01:00:24,579
Bring In-gang back!

675
01:00:24,662 --> 01:00:26,331
- Bring him back!
- Bring him back!

676
01:00:26,414 --> 01:00:28,499
Take responsibility, Longstar!

677
01:00:28,583 --> 01:00:30,585
- Take responsibility!
- Take responsibility!

678
01:00:30,668 --> 01:00:32,378
Bring In-gang back!

679
01:00:32,462 --> 01:00:34,380
- Bring him back!
- Bring him back!

680
01:00:34,464 --> 01:00:35,465
Baek Ah-jin!

681
01:00:36,716 --> 01:00:39,010
- Bring him back.
- Bring In-gang back.

682
01:00:39,761 --> 01:00:41,679
- Devil!
- You're the worst!

683
01:00:42,388 --> 01:00:43,931
Who are you? Move!

684
01:00:44,515 --> 01:00:46,851
I was her classmate.

685
01:00:46,934 --> 01:00:48,728
She doesn't deserve all this insult!

686
01:00:48,811 --> 01:00:50,855
- Where do you think you're going?
- Go away!

687
01:00:50,938 --> 01:00:53,441
- Come back here!
- Baek Ah-jin!

688
01:00:53,524 --> 01:00:56,152
- You're a devil!
- Bring him back to life!

689
01:00:57,111 --> 01:01:00,156
- Stop!
- Bring In-gang back!

690
01:01:00,448 --> 01:01:01,949
- Get away from her!
- Come here!

691
01:01:03,076 --> 01:01:04,786
Who the heck is she?

692
01:01:10,166 --> 01:01:13,252
Hey, I'm all filthy because of you,
so let me wash up first.

693
01:01:14,420 --> 01:01:15,963
Seriously.

694
01:01:16,798 --> 01:01:17,799
Hey.

695
01:01:23,054 --> 01:01:25,348
You have a nice place.

696
01:01:45,993 --> 01:01:47,662
So fancy.

697
01:01:48,663 --> 01:01:49,664
This is insane.

698
01:01:53,084 --> 01:01:55,044
You have lots of nice clothes.

699
01:01:57,964 --> 01:01:59,173
I missed you.

700
01:02:00,049 --> 01:02:01,926
Not bad for an orphan.

701
01:02:03,720 --> 01:02:05,304
You're successful now.

702
01:02:05,388 --> 01:02:06,681
Impressive, friend.

703
01:02:12,562 --> 01:02:15,606
Bring me some booze.
You drink, right?

704
01:02:16,566 --> 01:02:17,567
Right?

705
01:02:22,613 --> 01:02:23,656
Get out of my house.

706
01:02:27,326 --> 01:02:29,370
You used to run loan-shark schemes
on kids back in school

707
01:02:29,454 --> 01:02:31,497
and now look at you.

708
01:02:34,709 --> 01:02:36,419
Let me try that scheme, too.

709
01:02:37,962 --> 01:02:39,172
How about 100,000 won a day?

710
01:02:44,635 --> 01:02:47,513
Don't pick fights you can't win,
and get out.

711
01:02:51,476 --> 01:02:52,477
Fine.

712
01:02:53,060 --> 01:02:54,061
For now...

713
01:02:57,440 --> 01:02:59,066
I'll take this and call it even.

714
01:03:06,783 --> 01:03:08,493
The public sentiment
is extremely negative.

715
01:03:08,576 --> 01:03:11,329
Longstar also hasn't made
a clear statement yet

716
01:03:11,412 --> 01:03:13,456
so speculative articles
are flooding in.

717
01:03:15,249 --> 01:03:19,086
The agency's actor is under attack,
and they're merely watching?

718
01:03:31,682 --> 01:03:33,976
I know you were digging
into Ah-jin's father's death

719
01:03:34,060 --> 01:03:36,312
and stopped
when you started working with her.

720
01:03:38,439 --> 01:03:40,441
I suggest you work with me now.

721
01:03:43,611 --> 01:03:45,905
We may not be able
to reopen the whole case

722
01:03:45,988 --> 01:03:47,824
but this will be enough
to drag her down

723
01:03:47,907 --> 01:03:49,617
since she lives off public image.

724
01:03:50,910 --> 01:03:52,119
Is this everything?

725
01:03:52,203 --> 01:03:53,412
Just a portion.

726
01:03:54,372 --> 01:03:57,458
I'll give you the rest
as soon as you agree.

727
01:03:58,000 --> 01:04:00,419
Think about it and get back to me.

728
01:04:01,671 --> 01:04:02,880
Ms. Seo.

729
01:04:04,382 --> 01:04:06,300
You do know timing is everything
with exposés, right?

730
01:04:06,384 --> 01:04:07,552
About that timing...

731
01:04:08,886 --> 01:04:11,138
The sooner, the better.

732
01:04:49,135 --> 01:04:50,261
What are you doing?

733
01:04:51,596 --> 01:04:52,597
I'm sorry.

734
01:04:54,307 --> 01:04:55,308
Ah-jin.

735
01:04:56,767 --> 01:04:58,477
Is this a new persona
you're trying out?

736
01:05:01,731 --> 01:05:03,232
Sorry about what, exactly?

737
01:05:04,567 --> 01:05:07,028
I truly want to apologize.

738
01:05:10,698 --> 01:05:12,158
For everything I've done...

739
01:05:14,744 --> 01:05:15,912
I'm sorry.

740
01:05:17,747 --> 01:05:18,748
Ah-jin.

741
01:05:20,625 --> 01:05:21,626
After all this time?

742
01:05:33,220 --> 01:05:35,097
I'm even on my knees.

743
01:05:38,142 --> 01:05:41,228
Won't you please accept my apology?

744
01:05:42,647 --> 01:05:43,648
Please?

745
01:05:57,411 --> 01:05:58,412
Why should I?

746
01:05:59,997 --> 01:06:02,541
Why should I accept your apology?

747
01:06:06,212 --> 01:06:07,213
Ms. Hwang.

748
01:06:07,838 --> 01:06:09,340
For kneeling once?

749
01:06:11,175 --> 01:06:13,135
Considering everything
you've done to me

750
01:06:13,219 --> 01:06:15,721
your knees should be
worn down to the bones.

751
01:06:20,559 --> 01:06:22,228
Deep down, you've been waiting

752
01:06:23,396 --> 01:06:24,647
for my apology.

753
01:06:30,444 --> 01:06:31,612
I don't need it.

754
01:06:34,782 --> 01:06:35,783
Is that right?

755
01:06:41,163 --> 01:06:42,748
Well, I apologized.

756
01:06:49,296 --> 01:06:51,173
Don't forget to tell Jun-seo

757
01:06:52,133 --> 01:06:54,552
that I came and apologized.

758
01:06:57,513 --> 01:06:59,306
Make sure he knows

759
01:07:00,391 --> 01:07:01,517
I got on my knees.

760
01:08:42,827 --> 01:08:43,828
Do you know...

761
01:08:48,082 --> 01:08:50,876
when I hated you the most?

762
01:09:16,819 --> 01:09:19,405
I asked what you did to my grandma!

763
01:09:21,240 --> 01:09:22,366
I admit

764
01:09:23,325 --> 01:09:26,328
that was my intention at first.

765
01:09:28,789 --> 01:09:30,040
But...

766
01:09:36,130 --> 01:09:37,548
I liked

767
01:09:38,841 --> 01:09:40,259
In-gang so much.

768
01:09:44,096 --> 01:09:45,306
So, I...

769
01:09:48,767 --> 01:09:52,354
wanted you to love me, too.

770
01:10:02,323 --> 01:10:04,408
I'll take care of it.

771
01:10:10,623 --> 01:10:12,416
I'll tell

772
01:10:14,293 --> 01:10:16,503
In-gang the truth...

773
01:10:20,174 --> 01:10:21,508
and end this.

774
01:10:29,850 --> 01:10:31,101
Look at me.

775
01:10:44,240 --> 01:10:46,158
I still stand by it.

776
01:10:50,037 --> 01:10:51,038
The fact

777
01:10:52,623 --> 01:10:54,458
that you're also one of my children

778
01:10:55,918 --> 01:10:58,003
just like In-gang and In-mo.

779
01:11:00,047 --> 01:11:02,716
When your child does wrong,
you scold them

780
01:11:03,676 --> 01:11:05,261
and embrace them again.

781
01:11:07,805 --> 01:11:09,265
That's what a parent does.

782
01:11:25,030 --> 01:11:26,282
Ah-jin.

783
01:11:27,616 --> 01:11:28,826
Baek Ah-jin.

784
01:11:30,744 --> 01:11:31,745
Yes?

785
01:11:32,830 --> 01:11:34,290
You did wrong, didn't you?

786
01:11:40,421 --> 01:11:42,172
You won't do it again, right?

787
01:11:48,762 --> 01:11:50,180
That's good enough.

788
01:11:53,267 --> 01:11:54,268
Ah-jin.

789
01:11:56,186 --> 01:11:57,980
Here's what we should do.

790
01:11:59,648 --> 01:12:03,485
We'll keep this just between us

791
01:12:04,403 --> 01:12:05,612
and never tell anyone.

792
01:12:15,497 --> 01:12:18,500
My other babies must have arrived.

793
01:12:25,799 --> 01:12:27,468
Do you want to meet them?

794
01:12:36,602 --> 01:12:37,686
I hated you the most

795
01:12:40,064 --> 01:12:42,483
when you were kind to me
every once in a while.

796
01:12:53,035 --> 01:12:55,162
Because I would be tricked
by your kindness

797
01:12:57,206 --> 01:12:59,458
and start to fall for it.

798
01:13:06,173 --> 01:13:08,842
I was afraid of having
even a tiny bit of false hope.

799
01:13:14,598 --> 01:13:16,016
That's what scared me.

800
01:14:13,866 --> 01:14:15,909
Come on. Come.

801
01:17:01,825 --> 01:17:03,452
But now I know for sure.

802
01:17:26,433 --> 01:17:28,727
It's all my fault.

803
01:17:31,271 --> 01:17:32,606
Save her life.

804
01:17:37,444 --> 01:17:39,321
Please save her life.

805
01:17:40,280 --> 01:17:41,865
In hell, hope is...

806
01:17:46,703 --> 01:17:48,580
something you should never hold onto.

807
01:18:53,353 --> 01:18:55,480
They don't seem to know
who we are yet.

808
01:18:55,564 --> 01:18:57,441
It looks like he followed us
by coincidence.

809
01:18:57,524 --> 01:18:59,818
She's hospitalized at the moment.

810
01:19:00,485 --> 01:19:01,653
What would you have me do?

811
01:19:05,115 --> 01:19:06,241
Let's observe for now.

812
01:19:07,576 --> 01:19:11,121
Find out exactly
how they're connected.

813
01:19:11,204 --> 01:19:12,205
Yes, sir.

814
01:20:28,406 --> 01:20:32,744
DEAR X

815
01:22:52,258 --> 01:22:54,260
Subtitles by Ho-young Yun
